# ESP32 firmware deploy

After building or changing ESP32 firmware, flash the device — do not leave compiled firmware only on disk.

## OTA (preferred when Wi-Fi service is on)

1. Confirm the ESP network port is visible:

```powershell
& "C:\Program Files\Arduino IDE\resources\app\lib\backend\resources\arduino-cli.exe" board list --format json
```

2. Compile with `PartitionScheme=no_fs` (see `firmware/esp32/README.md`).

3. Upload with `espota.exe` using the IP from `board list` or the app Devices → OTA Wi-Fi screen:

```powershell
cd <repo-root>
$buildPath = Join-Path (Get-Location) "firmware\esp32\injector_pulse_meter\build-no-fs"
$espIp = "192.168.1.139"   # replace with detected IP
& "$env:USERPROFILE\AppData\Local\Arduino15\packages\esp32\hardware\esp32\3.2.0\tools\espota.exe" -r -i $espIp -p 3232 "--auth=" -f "$buildPath\injector_pulse_meter.ino.bin"
```

## USB fallback

Use when OTA is unavailable:

```powershell
$buildPath = Join-Path (Get-Location) "firmware\esp32\injector_pulse_meter\build-no-fs"
& "C:\Program Files\Arduino IDE\resources\app\lib\backend\resources\arduino-cli.exe" upload -p COM5 --fqbn esp32:esp32:esp32:PartitionScheme=no_fs --input-dir $buildPath firmware\esp32\injector_pulse_meter
```

Replace `COM5` with the port from `arduino-cli board list`.
